      { question: "An oliguric AKI patient has K+ 6.8 mEq/L with peaked T waves. What is the FIRST intervention?", options: ["Kayexalate 30g PO", "IV calcium gluconate to stabilize the cardiac membrane", "Furosemide 80 mg IV", "Start CRRT"], correct: 1, rationale: "With ECG changes (peaked T waves), the first priority is cardiac membrane stabilization with IV calcium gluconate. This does not lower potassium but protects the heart from arrhythmia while other measures take effect." }
