    pearls: ["DIC is ALWAYS secondary - treating the underlying cause is the most important intervention", "The hallmark labs: LOW platelets + LOW fibrinogen + HIGH D-dimer + prolonged PT/INR + schistocytes on smear", "DIC paradox: the patient is simultaneously CLOTTING (organ ischemia) and BLEEDING (consumptive coagulopathy)", "Only replace blood products if the patient is ACTIVELY BLEEDING or requires a procedure - do not treat lab values alone", "Schistocytes on peripheral smear indicate microangiopathic hemolytic anemia from RBC fragmentation on fibrin strands"],
