      { question: "What is the MOST important treatment for DIC?", options: ["Heparin infusion", "Massive platelet transfusion", "Treating the underlying cause", "Aminocaproic acid"], correct: 2, rationale: "Treating the underlying cause (sepsis, obstetric emergency, malignancy) is the most important intervention in DIC. Blood product replacement is supportive but does not address the root cause driving the consumptive process." }
